public class HandledExceptionExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] numbers = { 1, 2, 3 };
        try {
            System.out.println(numbers[5]);
        } catch (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException e) {
            System.out.println("An exception occurred: " + e.getMessage());
        }
    }
}

In this second example, the exception is caught using a try-catch block, 
and a message is printed indicating that an exception occurred.
This prevents the program from crashing and provides more controlled error handling.
